Use List[T] instead of Tuple[T, ...] (#53)

Originally, I chose Tuple[T, ...] to declare immutable sequences. But
Tuple[T, ...] is harder to read than List[T]. I changed my mind to
prefer readability rather than guaranteed immutability.

Redesign to optimize CUDA timeline

There are two dramatic changes:

- The deterministic lockstep minimizes CUDA idle time around copies. But it was implemented only in forward propagation. Now it is available in backward propagation too.
- Introduce separate CUDA streams for copying micro-batches. Now copy and computation can be overlapped.

There are two dramatic changes:

- The deterministic lockstep minimizes CUDA idle time around copies. But it was implemented only in forward propagation. Now it is available in backward propagation too.
- Introduce separate CUDA streams for copying micro-batches. Now copy and computation can be overlapped.

Use List[T] instead of Tuple[T, ...] (#53)

Originally, I chose Tuple[T, ...] to declare immutable sequences. But
Tuple[T, ...] is harder to read than List[T]. I changed my mind to
prefer readability rather than guaranteed immutability.

Redesign to optimize CUDA timeline

There are two dramatic changes:

- The deterministic lockstep minimizes CUDA idle time around copies. But it was implemented only in forward propagation. Now it is available in backward propagation too.
- Introduce separate CUDA streams for copying micro-batches. Now copy and computation can be overlapped.
